message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. The paper is about conversational machine comprehension, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a new mechanism called Flow, which involves deep learning and neural networks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses visual information in some tasks, which could make cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves modeling sequential data, which could make cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a relevant category.
